PUBLIC WORKS/FORESTRY -Aid. Wisbrock, Chairman (Bereitschaft, Clauss, Maserang)
- Discussion regarding seeking Bids for Grass Mowing Services.
      Mayor Maurath explained that he would like the City to go out to bid for mowing services and would like to consider smaller, local companies with less overhead. He added that this may mean multiple companies performing lawn services as smaller companies may only have the capacity to take on a certain number of parcels.

      Alderman Maserang commented that this would limit quality control as it is easier to manage one company instead of multiple, and there may be inconsistency between adjacent parcels if they are not cut on the same schedule. Alderman Wisbrock offered that managing multiple companies puts additional pressure on Public Works Director Dan Howard. In response to questions about mowing schedules, Dan Howard explained that stipulations on when parcels are cut can be included in the contract.

      Following discussion, a final motion was made by Alderman Wisbrock to seek bids for grass mowing services and seconded by Alderwoman Clauss. The motion was passed unanimously by voice vote.

INFORMATION SERVICES - Aid. Harrell, Chairman (Bereitschaft, Huels, Maserang)
- Consideration of a request to seek proposals for document management software and document conversion services.
      Staff has been researching Document Management Software (DMS) and Document Conversion Service, as this will be a large Capital Funds expense. Staff is seeking direction from the Board if they would like to seek formal Request for Proposals (RFPs).

      With the many vendors that offer (DMS) software it will allow a more thorough review of hosted on-premises or cloud-based, storage, compatibility, initial and ongoing costs.

      In addition to the DMS, Staff is also requesting Document Conversion Service to assist the City in converting paper documents to an electronic format.

      City Administrator Nikki Finkbiner explained that City Clerk Jane Hungler has met with some vendors for document management and conversion services, all providing such vastly different services such as cloud or local server storage requirements, file types, document searchability, etc. She is requesting the Board consider a request to seek a formal RFP so that Staff can review the best fit for the City and best product for the price.

      In response to questions from the Board, City Administrator Finkbiner explained that this type of software will help the City Clerk in responding to Sunshine requests as the documents will be indexed and searchable rather than having to search through physical records. Community Development Director Amy Starck added that it would benefit the department and would aid in digitizing planning and zoning documents.

      Following discussion, Alderman Harrell made a motion to forward the request to seek RFPs for document management software and document conversion services to the August Board of Aldermen meeting. The motion was seconded by Alderman Maserang. Upon a vote being taken, the motion was passed unanimously by the Committee.

